\begin_layout Standard
Enthalpy is formally defined as the internal energy of a system added to
 the product of the pressure and the volume.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Enthalpy comprises a system's internal energy, which is the energy required
 to create the system, plus the amount of work required to make room for
 it by displacing its environment and establishing its volume and pressure
\end_layout

